# API Design Standards (API 设计规范)

Scope: all DTS inter-service and external APIs

## gRPC (Service-to-Service)

- All proto files in a shared `dts-proto` repository/module.
- Package naming: `dts.<service>.v1` (e.g., `dts.agent.v1`, `dts.ontology.v1`).
- Use proto3 syntax exclusively.
- Every RPC must include `RequestMetadata` field for JWT token and trace context.
- Error handling: use standard gRPC status codes + custom error details.
- Versioning: new major versions create new package (v1 → v2). Minor changes backward-compatible.
- Streaming: use server-side streaming for long-running operations (Agent execution, data export).

## REST (Frontend-to-Backend via Gateway)

- RESTful resource naming: `/api/v1/<resource>` (plural nouns).
- Standard HTTP methods: GET (read), POST (create), PUT (full update), PATCH (partial update), DELETE.
- Pagination: `?page=1&size=20` with response envelope `{ data: [], total: N, page: N }`.
- Filtering: `?filter=field:op:value` (e.g., `?filter=status:eq:active`).
- Error response: `{ code: "ERR_CODE", message: "human-readable", details: {} }`.
- All endpoints require Authorization header (JWT). dts-gateway enforces this.

## Event Schema (Kafka)

- Topic naming: `dts.<domain>.<event-type>` (e.g., `dts.ontology.type-created`, `dts.agent.step-completed`).
- Message format: JSON with CloudEvents envelope.
- Every event must include: id, source, type, time, subject, data.
- Schema evolution: add fields only (backward-compatible). Breaking changes create new topic version.
- Audit events topic: `dts.audit.operations` — consumed exclusively by dts-audit-log.

## API-First Workflow (Law 5)

1. Define proto / OpenAPI spec.
2. Review and approve spec.
3. Generate client/server stubs.
4. Implement server.
5. Write integration tests against spec.
6. Then (and only then) build frontend.
